<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/460: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to
                                        Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-19T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 19,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>1204. Your telegram No. 1166, March 14, 8 p.m. I do not think it
                                advisable to approach British and French Governments with regard to
                                arbitration between Chile and Peru at this time. Will communicate
                                further on this subject after receipt of reply from Robbins.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>